profile: The MacLaren Art Centre is the regional public art gallery serving the residents of Barrie, the County of Simcoe and the surrounding area. Located in downtown Barrie, the Gallery has a permanent collection of 27,376 works of art held in trust for the public and presents a year-round programme of world-class exhibitions, public art projects, education activities and special events. For more information, please visit www.maclarenart.com or call 705-721-9696.
hours: Monday-Friday: 10:00 am - 5:00 pm. Weekends: 10:00 am - 4:00 pm.

profile:
The “sustainable minded” creative force behind Leah’s company Design by
Size typically saves time and money on projects wherever possible by repurposing
existing items into a new look.
“I’m not the designer who says we need everything new,” says Leah, a
Barrie-based entrepreneur with a blog packed with DIY tips. “Sometimes spaces
just need to be reworked for a new perspective. I don’t want to just buy to throw out”
